cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically on synthesizing human-like sketches from natural images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper employs deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of perceptual similarity loss function, which could potentially place it in the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper involves image translation, which could also place it in the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
